As this is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole draws down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have existed for several years.
These are not really errors but rather the expression of an incomprehensible faanethosis on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You're caught up in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them he's taking part in illegal races across America.
You are sitting behind the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco and your mission is to arrive the first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on another route and the stages in different environments that are quite distinct from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers something identical.
Some environments are quite beautiful overhang even though the graphic technical level is the same as the previous series.
Finally, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very nice visually.
Tests are more than once in time with an atypical element.
For example in the desert you will find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you must be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to that, the different races are well organized behind each other.
There is only a small number, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the requested number of opponents (like in a classic race) and then run against the watch ( classic duel with the chronometer) and then wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
It's rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping on the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What's surprising is that there are fewer times like this than what you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is as well because this element is not likely to interfere and places itself, in the context described above, in the elements that approve the game.
The model of driving is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that currently there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you'll have to go and see elsewhere.
But although we can find better in the competition the model of driving goes very well with the type of racing design.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a certain time.
To the difference of the driving model, the collisions are not yet in progress.
We do not expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight overruns you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy shells.
Or you'll find yourself in tights.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
The restart is done so that when you broke your figure or you went out in the decor the game brings you back at the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, in case something doesn't happen as it should, something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and the solution must be found by remembering from memory the piece of itinerary in question.
The great hic of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that we must go through in a certain way if this does not happen.
Otherwise you meet on a given location "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or one minute in late.
What upsets you are the situations when you see easily passing the opponent between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and turn them around or brake them either.
