Opponents still have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you still have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
It gets the most annoying at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at any cost pass before you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the sight of other vehicles in the reverse direction and you collide a lot of times.
We can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it's clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's bad because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and the places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You need to watch out for petrol pumps on the routes because you can change cars however most of the time the one you have enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American bicycles for the right highways and super sports cars around exotics on the very technical routes, for example on the lake roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that are common to challenges and adventures.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects online with the Autolog function that compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult to understand is the situation of the last race of adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (this looks like) where you drive in the darkness on the tracks (this looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (pre-) and behind you comes a metro branch that sends you the car directly to the ferry.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is usually pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is troubling is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not take the level and in some cases tragically.
This mainly concerns accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is the choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the young audience a new soundtrack has been created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes, we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
