The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festival Festival Academica for the third time offers festivals that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The festival's closing is composed of two concerts organized on 17 November.
"The Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Of the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The festival is the concert of the Choeur des lycées and secondary classes that takes place with free entry on November 17 from 14 hours on the space in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening there is the concert "Students of velvets" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of higher schools occur as well as that of Charles University.
The aim of the Festival Academy is not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop creative cooperation of young people.
The principal organizer is the Czech-desired Union in cooperation with lycée Jan Kepler.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, mastic meetings, student learning and other activities.
All information on the Internet pages of the festival is available at www.festaademica.cz.
