Watson was for the firm so irreplaceable that after 40 years of leadership it was his son who occupied the chair of director Thomas Watson Junior.
Under its leadership IBM began the development of artificial intelligence and developed the first programming language.
In the 1960s IBM people and computers helped NASA guide flights in the cosmos - on Mercury, Saturne and in 1969 on the Moon.
Meanwhile in 1964 IBM developed the first family of computers - the IBM System/360.
The classic PC that determines the computer standard of the time with the name IBM 5150 arrived on the market in 1981.
Twenty years later IBM sold its computer factory to the Chinese company Lenovo, but purchased the company of Consulting Pricewaterhouse Coopers and began to deal with advice and services with high added value.
