Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali dactyloscopy writer went to history as the man who confirmed the death of Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these staff members is crucial.
On November 4th, a Californian ITC dactyloscopy writer passed to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Leader of the Farcs: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopes working in the local ITC offices, this week was the "availability" tour of Eliasar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where he often spent more than five days in the forest to reach the location where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000, he moved to the capital city of Valle and after taking appropriate courses, he specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e., palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano we had warned Eliasar to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected that one of them was the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the site of the corpse, he did not recognize him by his physical appearance, because this one was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian wolf, ink, taker and lantern, Eliasar compared the fingerprints of the body with those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was Alfonso Cano.
That same night, the man who came from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Defense Minister, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the supreme head of the Farcs.
Searching for fingerprints
For a Dactyloscope writer in Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Eliasar González at a press conference for the operation against Cano is very significant.
A lot of people don't know what we're doing.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without any margin of error, which can be crucial in resolving crimes.
Apart from identifying the corpses, the dactyloscopes support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of captured persons.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove part of a wall from a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to draw a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the print of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different flights," he recalls.
Prints may also exclude or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
We recently found a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation, it has been determined that a parent may be a suspect of the crime and indeed a mark on the bottle coincided.
Even if this doesn't guarantee that he's the killer, it's on the crime scene.
One ITC dactyloscope explained that "the fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a picker or strip is used to remove them.
Later, fingerprints are sent to Asif, the delicant database, or to the National Civil Register.
"The problem is that there are still many Colombians without papers," said the ITC expert.
He explained that everything is not how we show it in the CSI TV program.
Just as everything that shines is not gold, everything that you touch does not become forced into a footprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is made.
