And indeed, prospects are not encouraging at all.
The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) noted that the majority of member countries presented clearer signs of economic slowdown in September.
The indicator that anticipates the inflection points of the world economy has highlighted that the main powers are impeded.
Because this one has dropped four decimal places to 100.4 points, compared to 100.8 points in August.
